This is part of my **100 Days of Python journey** and demonstrates an early milestone:  
Learning how to control program flow and simulate basic decision-making.

print("Welcome to the MicroHard log-in portal.State your username and password.")
username = input("Username: ")
password = input ("Password: ")
if username == "admin" and password == "1234":
  print("Welcome, admin!")
elif username == "guest":
  print("Welcome, guest!")
else:
  print ("Welcome, user!")
